    <j.0:document_reference rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">PE/228978</j.0:document_reference>
    <j.2:build_info>cdm:3840  tdm:1523  xslt:3886 saxon:9.0.0.1J JVM:1.6.0_29 metaconvJar:3886 builddate:19/07/2012 19:20:55</j.2:build_info>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/cdm#entity_temporal"/>
    <j.0:reported_by rdf:resource="http://publications.europa.eu/resource/agent/Gordon%20ADAM"/>
    <j.0:event_part_of_dossier rdf:resource="http://publications.europa.eu/resource/pegase/137319"/>
    <j.0:part_of rdf:resource="http://publications.europa.eu/resource/pegase/137319"/>
    <j.0:event_legal_comment xml:lang="fr">The draft report was adopted unanimously as amended, although all three amendments (seeking to strengthen and develop internal connections in Spain and Greece) do not alter its substance. Mr ADAM, whilst expressing his overall agreement with the Commission's proposal, pointed to the difficulty in amending the list of projects of common interest, as a lengthy debate may then follow in the framework of co-decision and, therefore, adoption before the end of this legislature could be hampered. The report draws attention to the external dimension of trans-European networks and, in line with this, requests the Commission to submit a strategy paper on the technical measures that would be required to open the European electricity grid to supplies from the New Independent States. The report also calls on the Commission to assess in advance the likely problems regarding energy supply security to stem from the increasing interest of some Asian countries, such as China, in participating in the exploitation of oil reserves in Central Asia.</j.0:event_legal_comment>
    <j.0:event_legal_date rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#date">1999-02-23</j.0:event_legal_date>
    <j.0:date rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#date">1999-02-23</j.0:date>
    <j.0:event_legal_document_reference rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">PE/228978</j.0:event_legal_document_reference>
    <j.0:event_legal_document_reference rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">A4/1999/87</j.0:event_legal_document_reference>
    <j.0:event_reported_by_person rdf:resource="http://publications.europa.eu/resource/agent/Gordon%20ADAM"/>
    <j.0:gets_report_of rdf:resource="http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/corporate-body/EP_ITRE"/>
    <j.0:type rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Rapport Commission PE 1ère lecture</j.0:type>
    <j.0:event_legal_initiated_by_institution rdf:resource="http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/corporate-body/EP"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/cdm#event_legal"/>
    <j.0:document_reference rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">A4/1999/87</j.0:document_reference>
    <j.0:event_legal_part_of_dossier rdf:resource="http://publications.europa.eu/resource/pegase/137319"/>
    <j.0:has_type rdf:resource="http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/event/REP_R1_byEP_CMT"/>
    <j.0:event_legal_reported_by_person rdf:resource="http://publications.europa.eu/resource/agent/Gordon%20ADAM"/>
    <j.0:event_legal_type rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Rapport Commission PE 1ère lecture</j.0:event_legal_type>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/cdm#period"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/cdm#event"/>
    <j.0:event_date rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#date">1999-02-23</j.0:event_date>
    <j.0:event_has_type_concept_type_event rdf:resource="http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/event/REP_R1_byEP_CMT"/>
    <j.0:comment xml:lang="fr">The draft report was adopted unanimously as amended, although all three amendments (seeking to strengthen and develop internal connections in Spain and Greece) do not alter its substance. Mr ADAM, whilst expressing his overall agreement with the Commission's proposal, pointed to the difficulty in amending the list of projects of common interest, as a lengthy debate may then follow in the framework of co-decision and, therefore, adoption before the end of this legislature could be hampered. The report draws attention to the external dimension of trans-European networks and, in line with this, requests the Commission to submit a strategy paper on the technical measures that would be required to open the European electricity grid to supplies from the New Independent States. The report also calls on the Commission to assess in advance the likely problems regarding energy supply security to stem from the increasing interest of some Asian countries, such as China, in participating in the exploitation of oil reserves in Central Asia.</j.0:comment>
  </rdf:Description>
